                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240407-132-victim1233 t18240407-132-viclabel740"></join>. On the 20th of February I was in the parlour behind the shop, and heard the scales move. I got up, and saw the prisoner going to the door - the till was wide open. I ran and took hold of him in the shop, charged him with robbing the till; he denied it; I missed half-a crown from it, there being only one there. I sent for an officer; he then entreated me to forgive him, and said he would do so no more; a person came in, and I got her to fasten the door, but he contrived to open it and get out - I followed him for two hundred yards, crying Stop thief! and he was stopped.</p>


               <p>
            
